You are a coding agent working on RocketRide UI. Follow the design system and theming rules below for any UI, CSS, or component changes.

Design System Location
- Tokens: src/design-system/tokens.css
- Base styles: src/design-system/base.css
- Components: src/design-system/components.css
- App-specific styles: src/app.css

Theme System
- Themes are controlled via CSS variables and :root[data-theme="..."] overrides in src/design-system/tokens.css.
- Current themes: tungsten (default), singularity, orbital.
- Never hardcode theme colors directly in components or CSS. Always use design tokens:
  - Backgrounds: var(--color-bg-primary|secondary|tertiary)
  - Text: var(--color-text-primary|secondary|muted)
  - Accents: var(--color-accent-primary|secondary|peak|neutral)
  - Gradients: var(--gradient-hero|accent|axis|node-core)
  - Shadows: var(--shadow-subtle|glow)
- For alpha/opacity usage, use RGB tokens:
  - var(--color-accent-primary-rgb), etc, inside rgba(...).

Visual Language
- Keep the UI minimal and structured.
- Accents are controlled: use accent colors sparingly and intentionally.
- Avoid pure white or pure black unless already defined by tokens.
- Use gradient tokens only where they convey meaning (CTAs, focus, key states).

Component and CSS Guidelines
- Use the rr- prefixed class system and existing patterns in src/app.css and src/design-system/components.css.
- Match spacing, radii, and typography tokens.
- Prefer extending existing components/styles rather than introducing new patterns.
- Avoid inline styles for colors or layout unless necessary for React Flow rendering.

Sidebar Theme Picker
- Theme picker lives in Sidebar footer under API Keys.
- Uses the theme popover styles in src/app.css (rr-sidebar__popover--theme).
- Icon for theme picker uses the paint-bucket icon.

React Changes
- If adding new UI that needs theming, wire it through tokens and avoid hardcoded hex values.
- If adding a new theme, update tokens.css and sidebar theme options/swatch styling.
